data.enText: if a plant withers or sth withers it, it dries up and dies

data.chText: 这些草在温暖的阳光下枯死了。
data.enText: The grass had withered in the warm sun.

data.chText: 萎缩；（尤指渐渐）破灭，消失
data.enText: to become less or weaker, especially before disappearing completely

data.chText: 我们所有的希望都渐渐破灭了。
data.enText: All our hopes just withered away.

tr: wither, as with a loss of moisture

value.def: If someone or something withers, they become very weak.

example.ex: When he went into retirement, he visibly withered...
example.tran: 他到退休年龄时已老态毕现。

example.ex: Industries unable to modernize have been left to wither.
example.tran: 无法实现现代化的行业已经自行衰落。

example.ex: To see my body literally wither away before my eyes was exasperating.
example.tran: 眼见自己的身体日渐衰弱真是让人心烦。

value.def: If a flower or plant withers, it dries up and dies.

example.ex: The flowers in Isabel's room had withered...
example.tran: 伊莎贝尔房间里的花已经枯萎了。

example.ex: Farmers in the Midwest have watched their crops wither because of drought conditions.
example.tran: 美国中西部农民眼睁睁地看着他们的庄稼旱死。

example.ex: His fridge was bare apart from three very withered tomatoes.
example.tran: 他的冰箱里除了3个非常干瘪的西红柿外已经空空如也。

value.def: The highest part of a horse's back, behind its neck, is referred to as its withers .
